Diagnosis.
Species mostly black with short, appressed and yellowish pilosity, but not forming any specific pattern on thorax or abdomen (
Figs 1–2
). Upper frons mostly black, with two small yellowish areas at the level of anterior ocellus and other two ventrally; face with a long beak-like projection, mostly dark brown, but yellowish dorsally (
Figs 5–8
). Wing infuscate with dark brown along the anterior portion, darker on basal two-thirds (
Figs 12–13
). Abdomen with a semi-translucent area on distal margin of tergite 1 and most of tergite 2, in males (
Fig. 1
); same semi-translucent area but reduced in females (
Fig. 2
).

